Hi Every one today I have made my C++ final project , A console based / terminal baed C++ 2d game named terminal orguilt. 
This game is inspired by a famous game named "Space Shooter".
As a Semester level project the complexity f the game is slighly minimal and as it is my firt project so complexuty is according to it.
From this project I have learned the use of array and 2D Arrays in C++. How arras are handeled. What is index/position in array.
Learned the purpose and use of some in built Libraries like Windows.h, Conio.h, C.string etc.
File handling is not used for printing the maze , instead 2D array is used.
This game is made by me as my semester level final project at university of engeeniering and technology lahore.
In this game I have implemented the concepts of array, loops, if else statements. 
In this game grid is printed using 2 D array and that array is fixed. 
In this game player is printed using ascii art and the position of player and enemy both are decided by maze size. 
Enemes are printed randmly by the random function. 
The position of enemy and player firing is determined by player and enemy positions.
Gotoxy function is used for position.
Windows.h is used for colors and gotoxy.
string used for handling string statements. 
Player movement is carried out by GetAsyncKeyState(KEY) function.
